Using DDTC-internal@groups.io

A listserv is an email address that allows cross-communication between a group of people. Within a listserv, everyone emails the same email address, which then distributes the messages to each person within the list. Think of a listserv as a community forum that takes place in your email inbox.

Yahoo used to offer a listserv, Yahoo Groups, and Google still operates Google Groups. Both are listservs, as is groups.io, which has a much friendlier interface and much more powerful administrative options than the others.

To send an email to everyone in the ddtc-internal group, simply send an email to:

  • ddtc-internal@groups.io

Most people use groups.io as email by receiving each message in their inbox and replying via email. They may have never tried any other options. The fact that a listserv can be used so easily is an advantage. Not everybody is a computer whiz.

However, groups.io offers a web interface that lets you add a password so that you can log in with your browser and select different message delivery options, including choosing a digest (summary), emergency notices only, or no emails at all.

https://groups.io/g/ddtc-internal

Once you are logged in you will find all the messages that have ever been posted to the group. So even if you have never received ddtc-internal emails in your inbox, you can use the web interface to find something posted in the past. This is particularly helpful for new DDTC members who want to look at old correspondence:

Notice the hashtags? You can add a #hashtag to the subject of any message and that makes finding related messages easy if you are looking for, say, all messages having to do with the #environment or #guncontrol or any of the topics we've already assigned hashtags to:

You can "mute" message threads that don't interest you. And even if you don't use the web interface, you can mute messages from the footer of any email you've received:

If you'd like to use groups.io as a messaging app instead of email, there is an app for both Android and iOS.

  • https://apps.apple.com/us/app/groups-io-app/id1553820507

  • https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=io.groups.webapp
